The paper deals with online algorithms and optimal stopping theory, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also has implications for mechanism design, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The use of algorithms to make decisions in an online setting suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in its analysis of competitive ratios. Finally, the use of algorithms to allocate resources based on values suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
